                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 23: The countrys foreign exchange reserves climbed $899 million for the week ended January 15 to $285.16 billion. In the previous week, reserves stood at $284.26 billion. Foreign currency assets during the week went up $853 million to $260.25 billion from $259.40 billion in the week-ago period, the Reserve Bank said in its weekly statistical supplement. Foreign currency assets expressed in US dollar terms include the effect of appreciation or depreciation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen held in the reserves, the RBI said.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 23: All large companies with over Rs 1,000 crore net worth will have to comply with the International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) by April 2011, the government today said. A core group set up by the corporate affairs ministry has recommended that the new system be implemented in three phases from April next year.                                                                                                                          
